-- 
Coal Mine Explosion in China Leaves 13 Dead, Three Rescued, Xinhua Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-19T13:06:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/coal-mine-explosion-in-china-leaves-13-dead-three-rescued-xinhua-reports.html
A coal mine explosion in southwest
 China  has left 13 people dead, the official Xinhua news agency
said, citing local government officials.  The accident happened on Oct. 17 at a mine in Fengjie
county in the municipality of Chongqing, Xinhua said, citing a
statement from the municipal government. Three miners were
rescued, it said.  Six people have been detained in connection with the
explosion and police and work safety authorities are
investigating, according to the report.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nerys Avery at 
 navery2@bloomberg.net  